!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %title= 'Brendan Barr { Web Development }'
    %link{ :href => '/css/base.css', :rel => 'stylesheet' }
  %body
    
    %header        
      %h1 
        Brendan Barr
        %span{ :class => 'title' }!= "<span>{</span> Javascript Developer <span>}</span>"
      %nav
        %a{ :href => '#/projects', :id => 'project_link' } projects      
        %a{ :href => '#/bio', :id => 'bio_link' } bio
        %a{ :href => 'http://github.com/bbarr', :class => 'external' } github        
        %a{ :href => 'http://senselesslogic.com', :class => 'external' } blog
    
    #content

      %section{ :id => 'bio' }
        %p
          I am a front-end web developer living in the New York area. Currently, I am employed as a Senior Open Standards Developer at R/GA, where I 
          enjoy creating rich user-interfaces and experiences with javascript, HTML and CSS.
        %p
          For server-side work, I always lean towards Ruby and either MySQL or MongoDB. I have played around with Node, but I have yet to find 
          a good enough reason to use it for a project.

      %section{ :id => 'projects' }
      
        %ul
          - @projects.each do |p|
            %li
              .inner
                %img
                %h4= p['name']
                %p= p['desc']
                .links
                  - p['links'].each do |name, url|
                    %a{ :href => url, :class => 'external' }= name
      
      %section{ :id => 'contact' }
    
    %script{ :src => '/js/jquery.js' } 
    %script{ :src => '/js/bb.js' }